article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 96, Chattanooga 69
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- Andrew Goudelock scored 27 points and Tony White Jr. had 22 to lead College of Charleston to a 96-69 victory over Chattanooga in the quarterfinals of the Southern Conference Tournament on Saturday night. The game was stopped for several minutes with 11:14 remaining when Chattanooga's Ty Patterson collapsed in front of the bench during a timeout. Patterson, a 6-foot-6 senior from Anderson, S.C., was carried off on a stretcher and taken to Carolinas Medical Center, where his condition was listed as stable. Chattanooga coach John Shulman said he was told by medical personnel that Patterson's blood pressure rose and he was having trouble breathing, but "they weren't really sure what happened." College of Charleston (21-10) moved into a semifinal game against Appalachian State on Sunday. The Mocs (15-18) also got 15 points from DeAntre Jefferson.
